---
title: '<<Change Record title>>'
revision_summary: '<<Description of changes>>'

# ── Metadata schema ──────────────────────────────────────────
#
# User properties for freeform fields. These are edited directly
# in the frontmatter by the author. Checkin extracts them to
# .meta/ user_properties as usual.

schema:
  purpose:         { type: text, required: true }
  impact_analysis: { type: text }
  references:      { type: text }

# ── Interaction graph ────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Organized into zones. Each zone name corresponds to an
# <!-- @interactive: name --> marker in the body below.
#
# Zones can declare sub-workflows for different lifecycle phases:
#   authoring  — active during DRAFT (build the content)
#   execution  — active during IN_EXECUTION (act on the content)
#
# The engine selects the active phase from the document state.

graph:
  zones:

    ei_table:

      # ── Authoring phase (DRAFT) ──
      # Build the EI table interactively.
      authoring:
        collection: true
        nodes:
          ei_type:
            values: [Implementation, Verification, Documentation]
            prompt: "What type of execution item is this?"

          ei_description:
            prompt: |
              Describe what this execution item accomplishes.
              Be specific enough that a reviewer can determine
              when this item is complete.

          ei_acceptance:
            prompt: >
              What are the acceptance criteria for this item?
              State observable, testable conditions.

          add_another:
            values: [yes, no]
            prompt: "Add another execution item?"
            yes: ei_type
            no: ~

      # ── Execution phase (IN_EXECUTION) ──
      # Complete each EI built during authoring.
      execution:
        each: ei_table
        nodes:
          ei_status:
            values: [Complete, Blocked, Deferred]
            prompt: >
              What is the status of EI-{{ item.index }}:
              {{ item.ei_description }}?

          ei_evidence:
            prompt: "Provide evidence of completion for this item."
            commit: true

          ei_completed_at:
            stamp: true
---

{# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
   RENDITION TEMPLATE

   This body serves double duty:
     1. During interaction, the Jinja2 between @interactive markers
        is evaluated with items collected so far to provide context
        above the current prompt.
     2. After all phases complete, the full body is rendered as the
        final document.

   The template must render gracefully with partial data — during
   authoring, execution fields don't exist yet; during execution,
   they're filled in incrementally. Use default() for fields that
   may be absent.

   Data sources:
     - Freeform fields (purpose, etc.) come from user_properties
     - Interactive zone data (ei_table) comes from interaction.*
     - System fields (doc_id, etc.) come from document metadata
   ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ #}

